description.value: Tobacco smoking increases serum levels of carboxyhemoglobin, carbon monoxide, and cadmium. This list of chemicals in tobacco smoke was based on "Cigarette Smoking" by Hecht SS, Samet JM. [Rom, p. 1521-51]
